values:
Well, I haven't been here for ages. i was expecting that my account would have been shut down by now - luckily not - at least posting here will mean it stays open for a while.
  I would have posted before, but I really haven't had anything much to say. If I have a thought, I will let you know. ok?

I'm supposed to be looking for a job today. 

I've applied for a job folding cloth. The man told me it "was a shit job, soul destroying and that i'd want to kill myself within two days of working there". Doesn't matter though - I'd take the job...
   I've also applied to have my brain scanned, be a sperm donor, impersonate Sherlock Holmes, be a bouncer in Surrey, be a waiter in the Groucho Club. I will get none of these gimmicky jobs - but at least I gave it a shot, eh?
  I want to get money together in order to afford smoking, drinking, spending a summer in london, getting a ticket to leeds festival, etc. Not to mention going back to university in October. In some ways I'd rather stay at home in London and not go back to uni - it's better in lots of ways - but usually better if you've got money. 
  Oh well, York Uni it is. You've probably never been to York unless you are (a) old or (b) a tourist who likes old things. York is small. Most people say it is pretty, and i suppose it is pretty. But lots of things are pretty and nice to look at.

This is my first entry on Live Journal. How exciting. Thanks to the person that gave away their code -i really appreciate it and will return the favour someday.

Erm, I'm new to this...I've never kept a diary before...could never be bothered....but this will improve my writing and will-power, won't it? 

Well, my name's Alex and I'm 20 (see how I'm slowly revealing fascinating information about my life). Stay tuned for more fascinating information.
